I think people do a lot
of flying of seaplanes

00:22:57.120 --> 00:22:58.620
up in the Great Lakes.

00:22:58.620 --> 00:23:00.900
But there again, the Great
Lakes-- there are harbors.

00:23:00.900 --> 00:23:01.920
There are calmer areas.

00:23:01.920 --> 00:23:03.485
So I think they're
not really landing

00:23:03.485 --> 00:23:04.860
in the middle of
the Great Lakes.

00:23:04.860 --> 00:23:06.750
And then, they don't
say, I just want

00:23:06.750 --> 00:23:09.300
to go to the middle of
Lake Superior and fish

00:23:09.300 --> 00:23:10.470
off the float for a while.

00:23:10.470 --> 00:23:12.060
They're going to
some destination,

00:23:12.060 --> 00:23:14.400
and by definition,
the destination

00:23:14.400 --> 00:23:20.340
will have a calmer area
for boats to hang out in.

00:23:20.340 --> 00:23:23.190
I think there's actually
a commercial seaplane

00:23:23.190 --> 00:23:28.820
service that's starting up
between Manhattan and Boston.

00:23:28.820 --> 00:23:30.900
So you'll go to the--

00:23:30.900 --> 00:23:32.782
there's a seaplane--

00:23:32.782 --> 00:23:33.990
I should have mentioned this.

00:23:33.990 --> 00:23:36.707
For helicopters, there are
helipads all around Manhattan.

00:23:36.707 --> 00:23:38.790
So you can actually go to
the downtown Wall Street

00:23:38.790 --> 00:23:40.725
heliport, land--

